comment.shortText:
Turbulence is a variable automatically provided inside of Turbulence test plans.  It is the entry point for all
tests, and allows test plans to be defined.
Start a new test.

An object allowing configuration of average response time criteria for a test.  Returned by the
[[Criteria.averageResponseTime]] method
Require that the average response times during the test were greater than the specified time.
Require that the average response times during the test were less than the specified time.

Allows criteria to be defined that will fail the test if certain thresholds are violated.  Injected automatically
into the [[TestPlan.breaker]] function.

Configure the average response time object.  Returns an [[AverageResponseTime]] object that allows further
configuration.

A freeform predicate that can evaulate the entire [[SummaryResults]] object that records the executed test plan.
The predicate should return either true or false to pass or fail the test respectively.
Returned from within an If block.  Allows alternate steps to be defined if the If predicate evaluates to false.
End the If statement.

A variable holder that can be injected into any function that supports injection.  It is used to share variables
between virtual users and test plans.  Variables can be attached like any normal JS object
(e.g. Global.myCustomVariable = 'MyValue';)
A class containing the http response returned by the server.
Get the body of the http response.
Get the status code of the http response as a number.
Steps to execute if the predicate evalutes to false.
End the if statement and return to the parent step chain.
End the loop and return the parent object.
An object maintaining a record of all responses Turbulence received over the course of a test.
Return the average response time for all requests.
An individual test plan.  It allows steps of the test to be defined in order.
How often to create a new user in milliseconds.  Cannot be combined with [[concurrentUsers]].

A function that determines whether or not to 'break' the Turbulence test (by returning a non-zero return code).
The function is passed the results object of the run and should return either true or false to indicate if the
run was successful or not, respectively.

comment.text: The function that configures the build criteria.

comment.shortText:
Set the number of concurrent users to simulate during this test.  Use in conjunction with [[rampUpPeriod]] to
slowly add load as the test runs.  Cannot be combined with [[arrivalRate]]
The duration of the test in milliseconds.
End this test plan and return the main [[Turbulence]] object.
Add a listener to the test.  See the {Listener} interface for information on what fields are necessary.

A warm-up period during which new users are slowly added to the performance test.  Use in conjunction with
[[concurrentUsers]].
The interface that listeners must adher to.
A function that produces a sample.

The common interface that all step creating 'nodes' implement.  These steps will be available when you have just
created a [[TestPlan]], entered an if statement, or started a loop.

Allows a predicate to be provided that can make an assertino against the [[HttpResponse]] returned in a previous
step and return True or False.

Assert that the Http request returned with the specified status code.  If not, this step will be marked as a
failure in the report.

comment.text: The Http status code to expect as a number

comment.shortText: Make an http GET request to the specified Url.

comment.text: The url to send the request to.
A label for this request.  This is shown in the standard Turbulence Html Reporter.  Purely cosmetic.

comment.shortText:
Start an [[IfStep]].  An if step evaluates the predicate that is passed in before decided to execute.  If the
predicate evaluates to false, the contents of the [[IfStep]] will not execute.

comment.text: The predicate to evaluate.  It is passed the result of the last step executed.

comment.shortText:
Start a loop for the specified number of times.  Steps can be chained off of this object until
[[LoopStep.endLoop]] is called.

comment.text: How many times to execute the contents of the loop.

comment.shortText: Pause the test execution for a set number of milliseconds.  Only applies to the current 'user'.

comment.text: The amount of time to pause in milliseconds.

comment.shortText: Send an Http POST request to the specified Url.

comment.text: The url to send the request to.
A label for this request.  This is shown in the standard Turbulence Html Reporter.  Purely cosmetic.

comment.shortText:
As [[EmbeddableStepCreator.pause]], except it pauses a random amount of time between the specified lower and
upper bonudaries.
